<br>
<br>
Melees describe weapons in terms of dmg/dly ratios.<br>
<br>
A 15 20 is a .75 weapon max haste which is only achievable buffed is 100% a .75 weapon with 100% haste becomes 1.5<br>
<br>
A 15 25 weapon is a .6 weapon with 40% haste it becomes .84<br>
<br>
This isn't even considering the pre 50 rogues that would be even worse off than the high end rogues. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A> at: 2/22/02 7:27:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/22/02 11:49:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whats the purpose of the 66% nerf</span><hr size=1> People from Rallos Zek should remember to mention that its there they are talking about, not pvp in general. 1 in 4 server doesnt qualify as the standard (thats not even counting duels on blue servers). The simple fact is that manaburn is unbalanced on Rallos Zek, among alot of other things. But this has little to do with balance on the other 3 pvp servers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 7:16:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whats the purpose of the 66% nerf</span><hr size=1> Pvp on blue servers is a non issue.  You don't have to pvp we do.<br>
<br>
I don't think mannaburn is balanced on ANY pvp server and wont be till its nerfed in pvp.  Admittedly its a much bigger problem on an item loot server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 12:05:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whats the purpose of the 66% nerf</span><hr size=1> If you are going into pvp bagged, you are asking for a beating. Also, mellees, being able to run the same speed as wizards, can make the wizards attempts to nuke just as useless as the wizard can make your attempt to mellee. The unbalance that I don't think can really be questioned is the healers against wizards. As it is, at some levels pvping against wizards on my shaman while fully geared didn't even concern me.<br>
<br>
Vivitron <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 7:01:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whats the purpose of the 66% nerf</span><hr size=1> The ability to interupt with melee dmg is a balance issue.  If you want to avoid interuption you can...<br>
<br>
Shadowstep<br>
<br>
Strafe run<br>
<br>
Zig Zag<br>
<br>
Fly overhead with levitate<br>
<br>
Use sow potions so you have an edge speed wise<br>
<br>
Get run speed early, on for several lvls at least you will be dealing with tanks who run slower than you indoors<br>
<br>
Run places where there are 2 or more possible ways to go and drop a nuke on the tank as he starts to go the wrong way<br>
<br>
Lamers will also tend to exploit ghosting and line of sight<br>
<br>
Nuke him before he knows your there as the first shot or maybe shots will give you quite an advantage<br>
<br>
Wizards are not unbalanced because its possible to be interupted IF the tank hits you for all or most of the spells cast time. Knowing how to get spells off = knowing how to pvp with your wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/4/02 6:17:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well, that setles it ;P</span><hr size=1> I guess Wizards are balanced.  I have no idea why Verant would come out and say that they would be &quot;Taking a strong look at Caster balance as we had melee balance..&quot;<br>
<br>
I assume you received some enhancements in PvP as a direct result of this previous Melee fix ?<br>
<br>
So I guess mister Rogue would rather see his class get enhancements and leave wizards without adjustment...apparently, not only do we disagree with you, Verant does as well.<br>
<br>
Play a Wizard to 60 on a PvP server, then come back and re-read your post Mr. rogue.  Thanks.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/5/02 6:24:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, that setles it ;P</span><hr size=1> Rogues gained nothing in the melee balancing deal. We were found to be balanced dmg wise in pve (which we are). Pvp wasn't brought up in that discussion because it was pve that was being tuned.  The one thing that was changed as a result of the melee balancing thing was that a few more decent pre epic piercers were added to fill the gap between say a trak tooth and a ragebringer for those that haven't quested for their epic yet.<br>
<br>
Rogues also do not gain relative pvp strength via AA skills so I haven't the slightest clue what your talking about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/7/02 12:33:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, that setles it ;P</span><hr size=1> Q:<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
Rogues also do not gain relative pvp strength via AA skills so I haven't the slightest clue what your talking about. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Here you get a clue:<br>
<br>
Chaotic Stab: (1 skill level - cost 6 skill points) - This ability allows the Rogue to do his minimum backstab damage on any backstab attempt, even if that attempt is not made while behind the opponent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/7/02 9:11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, that setles it ;P</span><hr size=1> Minimum bs is only 120 and you can't double bs on a chaotic stab.  I would much rather try for a real backstab than hit a dinky 120 unless your standing with your back against a wall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/7/02 3:28:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Anyone else get the impression that the only thing that would make the rogue happy is to have all the cards stacked in his favor ?  (I.E.  Pre-manaburn)<br>
<br>
PvP isn't supposed to be fair as a Wizard right ?  The only other classes we are supposed to be able to kill effectively is other casters, right ?<br>
<br>
Be honest here..do you even acknowledge the restrictions of manaburn and the ridiculously vulnerable state it leaves a wizard in ?  Yes manaburn may = sure death in some scenarios...but it is more defensable than some of the other class attacks/gear.<br>
<br>
How about a 60 warrior with Fungi ?  How do I kill him without manaburn ?  What, I can't..but thats ok right ?  I think you need to redefine what fair is..in other words, it is usually a 2 way street. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/7/02 6:32:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> I don't feel that pvp was slanted to give rogues a huge advantage nor has it ever been.  Its a lot better than it used to be I can tell you that for sure.  Rogue vs a wizard pvp depends a lot on the battle ground.  Wide open spaces favor the wizard, confined ones favor the rogue.  I don't think this is unbalanced.<br>
<br>
Let me give you a quick definition of balance in pvp.  First off any idea of precise balance in pvp is futile.  What we're looking for is a fun aproximation.  <br>
<br>
Pvp between any 2 given classes is balanced when pvp is fun and challenging between them. One party may be favored offensively or defensively but not to the extent that either party feels like they are wasting their time.  Some lvl of difference is fun...its called a challenge.  Past a certain lvl of challenge it because BS and unfun. Take any class at 60 vs a 60 sk as an example of that.<br>
<br>
I don't think rogues are unbalanced vs any class at all though we are I think strong vs wizards.<br>
<br>
The 66% dmg nerf is fair entirely in wizard vs rogue pvp.  If you haven't noticed my suggestions in the thread 45 people looked at but nobody cared to reply to include a suggestion for adjusting that on a class by class , lvl range by lvl range basis btw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27>PVP Forum</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.3<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

